{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901659446,"sessionID":"ses_2840505bcffecELQTfkh1K5DKB","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfcd124001a2AXkxlNrqmLgy","messageID":"msg_d7bfcaa88001V3QOMyerxH8Mc9","sessionID":"ses_2840505bcffecELQTfkh1K5DKB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5b6a14c0e1b04f35820523d42cf4fd20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec.md — AR-040 Python SDK/CLI Tests\n2: \n3: ## AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI Tests\n4: \n5: **Module:** sdk-python/tests  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Base specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## OpenSpec Format\n13: \n14: Each requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## REQ-001: CodeInterpreterClient Initialization\n19: \n20: ### Description\n21: CodeInterpreterClient requires router_url and handles session creation/reuse via ControlPlaneClient.\n22: \n23: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n26: - **GIVEN** neither router_url argument nor ROUTER_URL environment variable is set\n27: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient.__init__ is called\n28: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"router_url must be provided\"\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n31: - **GIVEN** ROUTER_URL environment variable is set to \"http://router\"\n32: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized without explicit router_url\n33: - **THEN** client.router_url equals \"http://router\"\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router URL explicit override\n36: - **GIVEN** ROUTER_URL environment variable is set\n37: - **AND** router_url argument is \"http://explicit-router\"\n38: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n39: - **THEN** client.router_url equals \"http://explicit-router\"\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Session created when not provided\n42: - **GIVEN** session_id argument is not provided\n43: - **AND** ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns \"session-123\"\n44: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n45: - **THEN** client._session_id equals \"session-123\"\n46: - **AND** client._session_created equals True\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Session reused when provided\n49: - **GIVEN** session_id argument is \"provided-session\"\n50: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterClient is initialized\n51: - **THEN** client._session_id equals \"provided-session\"\n52: - **AND** client._session_created equals False\n53: - **AND** no HTTP call to create_session is made\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure cleans up session\n56: - **GIVEN** session_id was not provided\n57: - **AND** create_session succeeded returning \"session-123\"\n58: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient initialization raises RuntimeError\n59: - **THEN** warning is logged\n60: - **AND** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n61: - **AND** session_id is set to None\n62: - **AND** RuntimeError is re-raised\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## REQ-002: CodeInterpreterClient Context Manager\n67: \n68: ### Description\n69: CodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol for automatic cleanup.\n70: \n71: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Context manager enters correctly\n74: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with valid configuration\n75: - **WHEN** entering context via \"with client as ctx\"\n76: - **THEN** __enter__ returns self\n77: - **AND** data plane client is initialized\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Context manager calls stop on exit\n80: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient in context manager\n81: - **WHEN** context block exits normally\n82: - **THEN** __exit__ calls stop()\n83: - **AND** data plane session is closed\n84: - **AND** control plane session is deleted if _session_created is True\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup on exception\n87: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient in context manager\n88: - **WHEN** exception occurs inside context block\n89: - **THEN** __exit__ still calls stop()\n90: - **AND** exception is propagated after cleanup\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## REQ-003: CodeInterpreterClient Stop Method\n95: \n96: ### Description\n97: stop() method closes data plane client and optionally deletes control plane session.\n98: \n99: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Stop closes data plane and deletes session when created\n102: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with _session_created=True and _session_id=\"session-123\"\n103: - **WHEN** stop() is called\n104: - **THEN** data plane client is closed and set to None\n105: - **AND** control plane delete_session is called\n106: - **AND** control plane client is closed\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Stop only closes when session was provided externally\n109: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with _session_created=False and _session_id=\"provided-session\"\n110: - **WHEN** stop() is called\n111: - **THEN** data plane client is closed\n112: - **AND** control plane delete_session is NOT called\n113: - **AND** control plane client is closed\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## REQ-004: CodeInterpreterClient Operations\n118: \n119: ### Description\n120: CodeInterpreterClient delegates operations to CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.\n121: \n122: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: execute_command delegates to data plane\n125: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n126: - **WHEN** execute_command(\"ls -la\") is called\n127: - **THEN** data plane execute_command is called with \"ls -la\"\n128: - **AND** return value matches data plane response stdout\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: run_code python execution path\n131: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with language=\"python\"\n132: - **WHEN** run_code(\"python\", \"print('Hello')\") is called\n133: - **THEN** timestamped .py file is written via write_file\n134: - **AND** execute_command is called with \"python3 <filename>\"\n135: - **AND** stdout from command is returned\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: run_code unsupported language\n138: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient\n139: - **WHEN** run_code(\"javascript\", \"console.log('test')\") is called\n140: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message matching \"Unsupported language\"\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: write_file delegates to data plane\n143: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n144: - **WHEN** write_file(\"content\", \"/workspace/test.py\") is called\n145: - **THEN** data plane write_file is called with same arguments\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: upload_file delegates to data plane\n148: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n149: - **AND** valid local file path\n150: - **WHEN** upload_file(local_path, remote_path) is called\n151: - **THEN** data plane upload_file is called with same arguments\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: download_file delegates to data plane\n154: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n155: - **WHEN** download_file(remote_path, local_path) is called\n156: - **THEN** data plane download_file is called with same arguments\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: list_files delegates to data plane\n159: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with initialized data plane client\n160: - **WHEN** list_files(\"/workspace\") is called\n161: - **THEN** data plane list_files is called with \"/workspace\"\n162: - **AND** return value matches data plane response\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## REQ-005: CodeInterpreterClient Verbose Mode\n167: \n168: ### Description\n169: Verbose flag controls logger level for debugging.\n170: \n171: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: verbose=False sets INFO level\n174: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with verbose=False\n175: - **WHEN** client is initialized\n176: - **THEN** logger level equals logging.INFO\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: verbose=True sets DEBUG level\n179: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterClient with verbose=True\n180: - **WHEN** client is initialized\n181: - **THEN** logger level equals logging.DEBUG\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## REQ-006: ControlPlaneClient Initialization\n186: \n187: ### Description\n188: ControlPlaneClient manages HTTP session for Workload Manager API calls with connection pooling.\n189: \n190: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Default timeout values\n193: - **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient without custom timeout\n194: - **WHEN** initialized\n195: - **THEN** timeout equals 120\n196: - **AND** connect_timeout equals 5.0\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: Custom timeout values\n199: - **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient with timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0\n200: - **WHEN** initialized\n201: - **THEN** timeout equals 60\n202: - **AND** connect_timeout equals 3.0\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Session created with headers\n205: - **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient\n206: - **WHEN** initialized\n207: - **THEN** requests.Session is created\n208: - **AND** Content-Type header is \"application/json\"\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: URL from explicit argument\n211: - **GIVEN** workload_manager_url=\"http://explicit-url\"\n212: - **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n213: - **THEN** base_url equals \"http://explicit-url\"\n214: \n215: #### Scenario: URL from environment variable\n216: - **GIVEN** WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL environment variable set to \"http://env-url\"\n217: - **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized without argument\n218: - **THEN** base_url equals \"http://env-url\"\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: URL required raises error\n221: - **GIVEN** no workload_manager_url argument and no WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var\n222: - **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n223: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"workload_manager_url must be provided\"\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## REQ-007: ControlPlaneClient Auth Token Resolution\n228: \n229: ### Description\n230: Authorization token is resolved from explicit argument or service account token file.\n231: \n232: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Auth token from explicit argument\n235: - **GIVEN** auth_token=\"explicit-token\"\n236: - **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n237: - **THEN** session Authorization header equals \"Bearer explicit-token\"\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Auth token from file\n240: - **GIVEN** read_token_from_file returns \"file-token\"\n241: - **AND** no explicit auth_token\n242: - **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n243: - **THEN** session Authorization header equals \"Bearer file-token\"\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Auth token empty\n246: - **GIVEN** read_token_from_file returns \"\"\n247: - **AND** no explicit auth_token\n248: - **WHEN** ControlPlaneClient is initialized\n249: - **THEN** Authorization header is NOT set in session\n250: \n251: ---\n252: \n253: ## REQ-008: ControlPlaneClient Create Session\n254: \n255: ### Description\n256: create_session POSTs to Workload Manager and returns session ID.\n257: \n258: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Create session success\n261: - **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient with base_url=\"http://wm\"\n262: - **AND** response contains {\"sessionId\": \"session-123\"}\n263: - **WHEN** create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"default\", ttl=3600) is called\n264: - **THEN** POST request to \"http://wm/v1/code-interpreter\" is made\n265: - **AND** JSON body contains name, namespace, ttl\n266: - **AND** return value equals \"session-123\"\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Create session missing sessionId\n269: - **GIVEN** response JSON does not contain \"sessionId\"\n270: - **WHEN** create_session is called\n271: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"sessionId not found\"\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Create session with metadata\n274: - **GIVEN** metadata={\"key\": \"value\"}\n275: - **WHEN** create_session is called with metadata\n276: - **THEN** JSON body includes metadata field\n277: \n278: #### Scenario: Create session metadata null\n279: - **GIVEN** no metadata provided\n280: - **WHEN** create_session is called\n281: - **THEN** JSON body includes metadata as null\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## REQ-009: ControlPlaneClient Delete Session\n286: \n287: ### Description\n288: delete_session handles DELETE request with special 404 handling.\n289: \n290: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Delete session success\n293: - **GIVEN** DELETE request succeeds with 200\n294: - **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n295: - **THEN** True is returned\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Delete session 404 returns True\n298: - **GIVEN** DELETE request returns 404 HTTPError\n299: - **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n300: - **THEN** True is returned (treated as success)\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Delete session other failure returns False\n303: - **GIVEN** DELETE request returns 500 HTTPError\n304: - **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n305: - **THEN** False is returned\n306: - **AND** error is logged\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: Delete session RequestException returns False\n309: - **GIVEN** requests.RequestException is raised\n310: - **WHEN** delete_session(\"session-123\") is called\n311: - **THEN** False is returned\n312: \n313: ---\n314: \n315: ## REQ-010: ControlPlaneClient Close\n316: \n317: ### Description\n318: close() method closes the HTTP session.\n319: \n320: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n321: \n322: #### Scenario: Close session\n323: - **GIVEN** ControlPlaneClient with active session\n324: - **WHEN** close() is called\n325: - **THEN** session.close() is called\n326: \n327: ---\n328: \n329: ## REQ-011: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Initialization\n330: \n331: ### Description\n332: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient requires session_id and base_url/router_url combination.\n333: \n334: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n335: \n336: #### Scenario: Init with session_id\n337: - **GIVEN** session_id=\"session-123\"\n338: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n339: - **THEN** client.session_id equals \"session-123\"\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Init with base_url\n342: - **GIVEN** base_url=\"http://router/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/test/invocations/\"\n343: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n344: - **THEN** client.base_url equals the provided base_url\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: Init missing params raises error\n347: - **GIVEN** neither base_url nor router_url provided\n348: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n349: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"Either base_url or router_url\"\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Base URL constructed from router_url\n352: - **GIVEN** router_url=\"http://router.example.com\", namespace=\"production\", cr_name=\"my-interpreter\"\n353: - **WHEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is initialized\n354: - **THEN** base_url equals \"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/production/code-interpreters/my-interpreter/invocations/\"\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ## REQ-012: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Session Header\n359: \n360: ### Description\n361: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all requests.\n362: \n363: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n364: \n365: #### Scenario: Session header lowercase\n366: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with session_id=\"session-123\"\n367: - **WHEN** client is initialized\n368: - **THEN** session headers contain \"x-agentcube-session-id\" (lowercase)\n369: - **AND** header value equals \"session-123\"\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ## REQ-013: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Execute Command\n374: \n375: ### Description\n376: execute_command POSTs JSON to api/execute endpoint with timeout handling.\n377: \n378: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Execute command success\n381: - **GIVEN** response contains {\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"output\"}\n382: - **WHEN** execute_command(\"python3 script.py\") is called\n383: - **THEN** POST to \"api/execute\" endpoint is made\n384: - **AND** return value equals \"output\"\n385: \n386: #### Scenario: Execute command JSON body\n387: - **GIVEN** timeout=30\n388: - **WHEN** execute_command(\"python3 script.py\", timeout=30) is called\n389: - **THEN** JSON body contains {\"command\": [\"python3\", \"script.py\"], \"timeout\": \"30s\"}\n390: \n391: #### Scenario: Execute command timeout buffer\n392: - **GIVEN** timeout=30 for command\n393: - **WHEN** execute_command is called\n394: - **THEN** read timeout equals 32.0 (timeout + 2.0 buffer)\n395: \n396: #### Scenario: Execute command non-zero exit raises error\n397: - **GIVEN** response contains {\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"error msg\"}\n398: - **WHEN** execute_command(\"cmd\") is called\n399: - **THEN** CommandExecutionError is raised\n400: - **AND** error.exit_code equals 1\n401: - **AND** error.stderr equals \"error msg\"\n402: \n403: #### Scenario: Execute command list input\n404: - **GIVEN** command passed as list [\"python3\", \"script.py\"]\n405: - **WHEN** execute_command is called\n406: - **THEN** JSON body command equals [\"python3\", \"script.py\"]\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Execute command default timeout\n409: - **GIVEN** client with timeout=120\n410: - **WHEN** execute_command(\"ls\") is called without timeout argument\n411: - **THEN** JSON body timeout equals \"120s\"\n412: - **AND** read timeout equals 122.0\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## REQ-014: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Write File\n417: \n418: ### Description\n419: write_file POSTs JSON with base64-encoded content to api/files.\n420: \n421: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: Write file base64 encoding\n424: - **GIVEN** content=\"hello world\"\n425: - **WHEN** write_file(\"hello world\", \"/workspace/test.py\") is called\n426: - **THEN** JSON body content equals base64-encoded \"hello world\"\n427: \n428: #### Scenario: Write file mode\n429: - **GIVEN** write_file called\n430: - **WHEN** request is made\n431: - **THEN** JSON body mode equals \"0644\"\n432: \n433: ---\n434: \n435: ## REQ-015: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Upload File\n436: \n437: ### Description\n438: upload_file POSTs multipart form data with session header.\n439: \n440: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n441: \n442: #### Scenario: Upload file multipart\n443: - **GIVEN** local file exists with content\n444: - **WHEN** upload_file(local_path, \"/workspace/test.txt\") is called\n445: - **THEN** multipart POST to \"api/files\" is made\n446: - **AND** files parameter contains the file\n447: - **AND** data parameter contains path\n448: \n449: #### Scenario: Upload file session header\n450: - **GIVEN** session_id=\"session-123\"\n451: - **WHEN** upload_file is called\n452: - **THEN** request headers contain x-agentcube-session-id=\"session-123\"\n453: \n454: #### Scenario: Upload file not found\n455: - **GIVEN** local file does not exist\n456: - **WHEN** upload_file is called\n457: - **THEN** FileNotFoundError is raised\n458: \n459: ---\n460: \n461: ## REQ-016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Download File\n462: \n463: ### Description\n464: download_file streams response and writes to local file.\n465: \n466: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n467: \n468: #### Scenario: Download file stream\n469: - **GIVEN** remote file exists\n470: - **WHEN** download_file(\"/workspace/source.txt\", local_path) is called\n471: - **THEN** GET request with stream=True is made\n472: - **AND** file content is written to local_path\n473: \n474: #### Scenario: Download file creates parent directory\n475: - **GIVEN** local_path in nonexistent subdirectory\n476: - **WHEN** download_file is called\n477: - **THEN** parent directory is created\n478: - **AND** file is written successfully\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Download file removes leading slash\n481: - **GIVEN** remote_path=\"/workspace/source.txt\"\n482: - **WHEN** download_file is called\n483: - **THEN** request URL contains \"source.txt\" (leading slash removed)\n484: \n485: ---\n486: \n487: ## REQ-017: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient List Files\n488: \n489: ### Description\n490: list_files GETs api/files with path query parameter.\n491: \n492: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n493: \n494: #### Scenario: List files with path\n495: - **GIVEN** response contains {\"files\": [\"file1.py\", \"file2.py\"]}\n496: - **WHEN** list_files(\"/workspace\") is called\n497: - **THEN** GET to \"api/files\" with params path=\"/workspace\"\n498: - **AND** return value equals {\"files\": [\"file1.py\", \"file2.py\"]}\n499: \n500: #### Scenario: List files default path\n501: - **GIVEN** no path argument\n502: - **WHEN** list_files() is called\n503: - **THEN** params path equals \".\" (default)\n504: \n505: ---\n506: \n507: ## REQ-018: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Close\n508: \n509: ### Description\n510: close() method closes the HTTP session.\n511: \n512: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n513: \n514: #### Scenario: Close session\n515: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient with active session\n516: - **WHEN** close() is called\n517: - **THEN** session.close() is called\n518: \n519: ---\n520: \n521: ## REQ-019: AgentRuntimeClient Initialization\n522: \n523: ### Description\n524: AgentRuntimeClient requires router_url and manages session bootstrap/reuse.\n525: \n526: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n527: \n528: #### Scenario: Init all parameters\n529: - **GIVEN** agent_name=\"test-agent\", namespace=\"test-ns\", router_url=\"http://router\", verbose=True, session_id=\"test-session\", timeout=60, connect_timeout=10.0\n530: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n531: - **THEN** all fields match provided values\n532: \n533: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n534: - **GIVEN** no router_url argument and no ROUTER_URL environment variable\n535: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n536: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"Router URL must be provided via argument or ROUTER_URL environment variable\"\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: Router URL from environment variable\n539: - **GIVEN** ROUTER_URL=\"http://router-env.example.com\"\n540: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized without router_url\n541: - **THEN** router_url equals \"http://router-env.example.com\"\n542: \n543: ---\n544: \n545: ## REQ-020: AgentRuntimeClient Session Bootstrap\n546: \n547: ### Description\n548: Session ID is bootstrapped from Router GET endpoint when not provided.\n549: \n550: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n551: \n552: #### Scenario: Session bootstrap from GET\n553: - **GIVEN** GET to invocations endpoint returns header x-agentcube-session-id=\"bootstrapped-session\"\n554: - **AND** no session_id argument provided\n555: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n556: - **THEN** session_id equals \"bootstrapped-session\"\n557: \n558: #### Scenario: Session reuse when provided\n559: - **GIVEN** session_id=\"provided-session\"\n560: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n561: - **THEN** session_id equals \"provided-session\"\n562: - **AND** no GET request is made\n563: \n564: ---\n565: \n566: ## REQ-021: AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager\n567: \n568: ### Description\n569: AgentRuntimeClient supports context manager protocol.\n570: \n571: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n572: \n573: #### Scenario: Context enter returns self\n574: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient\n575: - **WHEN** entering context\n576: - **THEN** __enter__ returns self\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Context exit calls close\n579: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient in context\n580: - **WHEN** context block exits\n581: - **THEN** close() is called\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: Context exit on exception calls close\n584: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient in context\n585: - **WHEN** exception occurs in context block\n586: - **THEN** close() is still called\n587: - **AND** exception is propagated\n588: \n589: ---\n590: \n591: ## REQ-022: AgentRuntimeClient Invoke\n592: \n593: ### Description\n594: invoke POSTs JSON payload to Agent Runtime endpoint.\n595: \n596: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n597: \n598: #### Scenario: Invoke delegates to data plane\n599: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with session_id=\"test-session\"\n600: - **AND** data plane returns {\"result\": \"success\"}\n601: - **WHEN** invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}) is called\n602: - **THEN** result equals {\"result\": \"success\"}\n603: \n604: #### Scenario: Invoke without session raises error\n605: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with session_id=None\n606: - **WHEN** invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}) is called\n607: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\"\n608: \n609: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout passthrough\n610: - **GIVEN** timeout=30 argument\n611: - **WHEN** invoke({\"input\": \"test\"}, timeout=30) is called\n612: - **THEN** data plane invoke receives timeout=30\n613: \n614: ---\n615: \n616: ## REQ-023: AgentRuntimeClient Close\n617: \n618: ### Description\n619: close() method closes the data plane client.\n620: \n621: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n622: \n623: #### Scenario: Close calls data plane close\n624: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with data plane client\n625: - **WHEN** close() is called\n626: - **THEN** data plane close() is called\n627: \n628: ---\n629: \n630: ## REQ-024: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Initialization\n631: \n632: ### Description\n633: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient manages HTTP session for Agent Runtime invocations.\n634: \n635: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n636: \n637: #### Scenario: Default timeout values\n638: - **GIVEN** no custom timeout arguments\n639: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n640: - **THEN** timeout equals 120\n641: - **AND** connect_timeout equals 5.0\n642: \n643: #### Scenario: Custom timeout values\n644: - **GIVEN** timeout=60, connect_timeout=10.0\n645: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n646: - **THEN** timeout equals 60\n647: - **AND** connect_timeout equals 10.0\n648: \n649: #### Scenario: Session header constant\n650: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient class\n651: - **WHEN** SESSION_HEADER is checked\n652: - **THEN** value equals \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n653: \n654: #### Scenario: Base URL construction\n655: - **GIVEN** router_url=\"http://router.example.com\", namespace=\"default\", agent_name=\"my-agent\"\n656: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is initialized\n657: - **THEN** base_url equals \"http://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/default/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/\"\n658: \n659: ---\n660: \n661: ## REQ-025: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Connection Pooling\n662: \n663: ### Description\n664: HTTP session uses HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n665: \n666: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n667: \n668: #### Scenario: Connection pooling adapters\n669: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n670: - **WHEN** session adapters are checked\n671: - **THEN** HTTPAdapter is mounted for http:// and https://\n672: \n673: ---\n674: \n675: ## REQ-026: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap Session ID\n676: \n677: ### Description\n678: bootstrap_session_id GETs invocation endpoint to obtain session header.\n679: \n680: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n681: \n682: #### Scenario: Bootstrap success\n683: - **GIVEN** GET returns header x-agentcube-session-id=\"test-session-123\"\n684: - **WHEN** bootstrap_session_id() is called\n685: - **THEN** return value equals \"test-session-123\"\n686: \n687: #### Scenario: Bootstrap missing header raises error\n688: - **GIVEN** GET response has no x-agentcube-session-id header\n689: - **WHEN** bootstrap_session_id() is called\n690: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with message \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n691: \n692: ---\n693: \n694: ## REQ-027: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke\n695: \n696: ### Description\n697: invoke POSTs JSON payload with session header.\n698: \n699: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n700: \n701: #### Scenario: Invoke with session\n702: - **GIVEN** session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n703: - **WHEN** invoke(\"test-session-123\", {\"input\": \"test\"}) is called\n704: - **THEN** POST to base_url is made\n705: - **AND** response object is returned\n706: \n707: #### Scenario: Invoke headers correct\n708: - **GIVEN** session_id=\"test-session-123\"\n709: - **WHEN** invoke is called\n710: - **THEN** request headers contain x-agentcube-session-id=\"test-session-123\"\n711: - **AND** request headers contain Content-Type=\"application/json\"\n712: \n713: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout override\n714: - **GIVEN** timeout=30 argument\n715: - **WHEN** invoke is called with timeout=30\n716: - **THEN** read timeout uses provided value\n717: \n718: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout default\n719: - **GIVEN** no timeout argument\n720: - **WHEN** invoke is called\n721: - **THEN** read timeout equals self.timeout (default 120)\n722: \n723: ---\n724: \n725: ## REQ-028: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Close\n726: \n727: ### Description\n728: close() method closes the HTTP session.\n729: \n730: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n731: \n732: #### Scenario: Close session\n733: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient with active session\n734: - **WHEN** close() is called\n735: - **THEN** session is closed\n736: \n737: ---\n738: \n739: ## REQ-029: Exception Hierarchy\n740: \n741: ### Description\n742: AgentCube SDK defines exception hierarchy for error handling.\n743: \n744: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n745: \n746: #### Scenario: AgentCubeError is Exception\n747: - **GIVEN** AgentCubeError class\n748: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n749: - **THEN** issubclass(AgentCubeError, Exception) equals True\n750: \n751: #### Scenario: CommandExecutionError is AgentCubeError\n752: - **GIVEN** CommandExecutionError class\n753: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n754: - **THEN** issubclass(CommandExecutionError, AgentCubeError) equals True\n755: \n756: #### Scenario: SessionError is AgentCubeError\n757: - **GIVEN** SessionError class\n758: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n759: - **THEN** issubclass(SessionError, AgentCubeError) equals True\n760: \n761: #### Scenario: DataPlaneError is AgentCubeError\n762: - **GIVEN** DataPlaneError class\n763: - **WHEN** inheritance is checked\n764: - **THEN** issubclass(DataPlaneError, AgentCubeError) equals True\n765: \n766: ---\n767: \n768: ## REQ-030: CommandExecutionError\n769: \n770: ### Description\n771: CommandExecutionError captures command failure details.\n772: \n773: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n774: \n775: #### Scenario: Constructor with all params\n776: - **GIVEN** exit_code=2, stderr=\"failed\", command=\"ls -la\"\n777: - **WHEN** CommandExecutionError is created\n778: - **THEN** error.exit_code equals 2\n779: - **AND** error.stderr equals \"failed\"\n780: - **AND** error.command equals \"ls -la\"\n781: \n782: #### Scenario: Constructor default command\n783: - **GIVEN** exit_code=1, stderr=\"error\" (no command)\n784: - **WHEN** CommandExecutionError is created\n785: - **THEN** error.command equals None\n786: \n787: #### Scenario: Message format\n788: - **GIVEN** exit_code=2, stderr=\"failed output\"\n789: - **WHEN** str(error) is called\n790: - **THEN** equals \"Command failed (exit 2): failed output\"\n791: \n792: ---\n793: \n794: ## REQ-031: SessionError and DataPlaneError\n795: \n796: ### Description\n797: SessionError and DataPlaneError are placeholder exception types.\n798: \n799: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n800: \n801: #### Scenario: SessionError docstring\n802: - **GIVEN** SessionError class\n803: - **WHEN** docstring is checked\n804: - **THEN** contains \"session\"\n805: \n806: #### Scenario: SessionError inherits from AgentCubeError\n807: - **GIVEN** SessionError instance\n808: - **WHEN** isinstance check is performed\n809: - **THEN** isinstance(error, AgentCubeError) equals True\n810: \n811: #### Scenario: DataPlaneError docstring\n812: - **GIVEN** DataPlaneError class\n813: - **WHEN** docstring is checked\n814: - **THEN** contains \"data plane\"\n815: \n816: #### Scenario: DataPlaneError inherits from AgentCubeError\n817: - **GIVEN** DataPlaneError instance\n818: - **WHEN** isinstance check is performed\n819: - **THEN** isinstance(error, AgentCubeError) equals True\n820: \n821: ---\n822: \n823: ## REQ-032: Package Exports\n824: \n825: ### Description\n826: Public package surface defines what users can import.\n827: \n828: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n829: \n830: #### Scenario: Root package exports CodeInterpreterClient\n831: - **GIVEN** from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n832: - **WHEN** import succeeds\n833: - **THEN** CodeInterpreterClient is available\n834: \n835: #### Scenario: Root package exports AgentRuntimeClient\n836: - **GIVEN** from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n837: - **WHEN** import succeeds\n838: - **THEN** AgentRuntimeClient is available\n839: \n840: #### Scenario: Root __all__ contains exactly two names\n841: - **GIVEN** agentcube.__all__\n842: - **WHEN** checked\n843: - **THEN** contains \"CodeInterpreterClient\" and \"AgentRuntimeClient\"\n844: - **AND** length equals 2\n845: \n846: #### Scenario: Clients package exports ControlPlaneClient\n847: - **GIVEN** from agentcube.clients import ControlPlaneClient\n848: - **WHEN** import succeeds\n849: - **THEN** ControlPlaneClient is available\n850: \n851: #### Scenario: Clients package exports CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n852: - **GIVEN** from agentcube.clients import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n853: - **WHEN** import succeeds\n854: - **THEN** CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient is available\n855: \n856: #### Scenario: Clients package exports AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n857: - **GIVEN** from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n858: - **WHEN** import succeeds\n859: - **THEN** AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient is available\n860: \n861: #### Scenario: Clients __all__ contains exactly three names\n862: - **GIVEN** agentcube.clients.__all__\n863: - **WHEN** checked\n864: - **THEN** contains ControlPlaneClient, CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient, AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n865: - **AND** length equals 3\n866: \n867: ---\n868: \n869: ## REQ-033: Utils - create_session\n870: \n871: ### Description\n872: create_session creates requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n873: \n874: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n875: \n876: #### Scenario: Returns requests.Session\n877: - **GIVEN** create_session() called\n878: - **WHEN** result is checked\n879: - **THEN** isinstance(result, requests.Session) equals True\n880: \n881: #### Scenario: Has adapters mounted\n882: - **GIVEN** session from create_session()\n883: - **WHEN** adapters are checked\n884: - **THEN** \"http://\" in session.adapters\n885: - **AND** \"https://\" in session.adapters\n886: \n887: #### Scenario: Custom pool settings\n888: - **GIVEN** pool_connections=5, pool_maxsize=5\n889: - **WHEN** create_session(5, 5) is called\n890: - **THEN** returns valid requests.Session\n891: \n892: ---\n893: \n894: ## REQ-034: Utils - read_token_from_file\n895: \n896: ### Description\n897: read_token_from_file reads and strips token from file.\n898: \n899: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n900: \n901: #### Scenario: Read token success\n902: - **GIVEN** file containing \"my-secret-token\\n\"\n903: - **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n904: - **THEN** returns \"my-secret-token\" (stripped)\n905: \n906: #### Scenario: Read token file not found\n907: - **GIVEN** nonexistent file path\n908: - **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n909: - **THEN** returns \"\"\n910: \n911: #### Scenario: Read token strip whitespace\n912: - **GIVEN** file containing \"  token-with-spaces  \\n\"\n913: - **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n914: - **THEN** returns \"token-with-spaces\"\n915: \n916: #### Scenario: Read token multiline preserves content\n917: - **GIVEN** file containing \"token-line1\\ntoken-line2\\n\"\n918: - **WHEN** read_token_from_file is called\n919: - **THEN** returns \"token-line1\\ntoken-line2\"\n920: \n921: ---\n922: \n923: ## REQ-035: Utils - get_logger\n924: \n925: ### Description\n926: get_logger creates named logger with configurable level.\n927: \n928: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n929: \n930: #### Scenario: Returns Logger\n931: - **GIVEN** get_logger(\"test_logger\") called\n932: - **WHEN** result is checked\n933: - **THEN** isinstance(result, logging.Logger) equals True\n934: - **AND** logger.name equals \"test_logger\"\n935: \n936: #### Scenario: Default level INFO\n937: - **GIVEN** get_logger without level argument\n938: - **WHEN** logger is created\n939: - **THEN** level equals logging.INFO\n940: \n941: #### Scenario: Custom level int\n942: - **GIVEN** level=logging.DEBUG\n943: - **WHEN** get_logger is called\n944: - **THEN** level equals logging.DEBUG\n945: \n946: #### Scenario: Custom level str\n947: - **GIVEN** level=\"DEBUG\"\n948: - **WHEN** get_logger is called\n949: - **THEN** level equals logging.DEBUG\n950: \n951: ---\n952: \n953: ## REQ-036: AgentRuntime Integration - Full Lifecycle\n954: \n955: ### Description\n956: Integration tests verify complete session lifecycle.\n957: \n958: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n959: \n960: #### Scenario: Full session lifecycle\n961: - **GIVEN** Router GET returns session header\n962: - **AND** Router POST returns success\n963: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient used as context manager\n964: - **THEN** session is bootstrapped\n965: - **AND** invoke returns correct result\n966: - **AND** cleanup happens on exit\n967: \n968: #### Scenario: Invoke workflow with payload\n969: - **GIVEN** valid AgentRuntimeClient\n970: - **WHEN** invoke({\"action\": \"process\", \"data\": \"input\"}) is called\n971: - **THEN** response payload is returned correctly\n972: \n973: #### Scenario: Session reuse across multiple invokes\n974: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimeClient with session\n975: - **WHEN** multiple invoke calls are made\n976: - **THEN** session_id remains constant\n977: - **AND** all invokes succeed\n978: \n979: #### Scenario: Bootstrap failure handling\n980: - **GIVEN** Router GET returns no session header\n981: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimeClient is initialized\n982: - **THEN** ValueError is raised with correct message\n983: \n984: #### Scenario: Invoke failure handling\n985: - **GIVEN** Router POST returns 500\n986: - **WHEN** invoke is called\n987: - **THEN** HTTPError is raised\n988: \n989: ---\n990: \n991: ## Summary\n992: \n993: | REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n994: |--------|-----------|------------|\n995: | REQ-001 | CodeInterpreterClient Init | 6 |\n996: | REQ-002 | CodeInterpreterClient Context Manager | 3 |\n997: | REQ-003 | CodeInterpreterClient Stop | 2 |\n998: | REQ-004 | CodeInterpreterClient Operations | 7 |\n999: | REQ-005 | CodeInterpreterClient Verbose | 2 |\n1000: | REQ-006 | ControlPlaneClient Init | 6 |\n1001: | REQ-007 | ControlPlaneClient Auth Token | 3 |\n1002: | REQ-008 | ControlPlaneClient Create Session | 4 |\n1003: | REQ-009 | ControlPlaneClient Delete Session | 4 |\n1004: | REQ-010 | ControlPlaneClient Close | 1 |\n1005: | REQ-011 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Init | 4 |\n1006: | REQ-012 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Session Header | 1 |\n1007: | REQ-013 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Execute Command | 6 |\n1008: | REQ-014 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Write File | 2 |\n1009: | REQ-015 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Upload File | 3 |\n1010: | REQ-016 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Download File | 3 |\n1011: | REQ-017 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient List Files | 2 |\n1012: | REQ-018 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Close | 1 |\n1013: | REQ-019 | AgentRuntimeClient Init | 3 |\n1014: | REQ-020 | AgentRuntimeClient Session Bootstrap | 2 |\n1015: | REQ-021 | AgentRuntimeClient Context Manager | 3 |\n1016: | REQ-022 | AgentRuntimeClient Invoke | 3 |\n1017: | REQ-023 | AgentRuntimeClient Close | 1 |\n1018: | REQ-024 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Init | 4 |\n1019: | REQ-025 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Pooling | 1 |\n1020: | REQ-026 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Bootstrap | 2 |\n1021: | REQ-027 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Invoke | 4 |\n1022: | REQ-028 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Close | 1 |\n1023: | REQ-029 | Exception Hierarchy | 4 |\n1024: | REQ-030 | CommandExecutionError | 3 |\n1025: | REQ-031 | SessionError/DataPlaneError | 4 |\n1026: | REQ-032 | Package Exports | 7 |\n1027: | REQ-033 | Utils create_session | 3 |\n1028: | REQ-034 | Utils read_token_from_file | 4 |\n1029: | REQ-035 | Utils get_logger | 4 |\n1030: | REQ-036 | AgentRuntime Integration | 5 |\n1031: \n1032: **Total Scenarios:** 104\n1033: \n1034: ---\n1035: \n1036: ## Implementation Files\n1037: \n1038: | Path | Role |\n1039: |------|------|\n1040: | `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py` | Root package exports |\n1041: | `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | CodeInterpreterClient |\n1042: | `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | AgentRuntimeClient |\n1043: | `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n1044: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Clients package exports |\n1045: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | ControlPlaneClient |\n1046: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n1047: | `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n1048: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py` | create_session |\n1049: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py` | read_token_from_file |\n1050: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py` | get_logger |\n1051: \n1052: ---\n1053: \n1054: ## Test Files (Existing)\n1055: \n1056: | Path | Coverage |\n1057: |------|----------|\n1058: | `sdk-python/tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle |\n1059: | `sdk-python/tests/test_control_plane.py` | ControlPlaneClient HTTP |\n1060: | `sdk-python/tests/test_data_plane.py` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n1061: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | AgentRuntimeClient |\n1062: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient |\n1063: | `sdk-python/tests/test_exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n1064: | `sdk-python/tests/test_exports.py` | Package exports |\n1065: | `sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py` | Utility functions |\n1066: | `sdk-python/tests/test_agent_runtime_integration.py` | Integration tests |\n1067: \n1068: ---\n1069: \n1070: ## Dependencies\n1071: \n1072: | Dependency | Purpose |\n1073: |------------|---------|\n1074: | `pytest` | Test framework |\n1075: | `responses` | HTTP mocking |\n1076: | `requests` | HTTP client |\n1077: \n1078: ---\n1079: \n1080: ## Validation Checklist\n1081: \n1082: - [ ] CodeInterpreterClient router_url required and resolution\n1083: - [ ] CodeInterpreterClient session creation and reuse\n1084: - [ ] CodeInterpreterClient context manager cleanup\n1085: - [ ] CodeInterpreterClient operation delegation\n1086: - [ ] ControlPlaneClient HTTP session management\n1087: - [ ] ControlPlaneClient auth token resolution\n1088: - [ ] ControlPlaneClient create/delete session\n1089: - [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient base URL construction\n1090: - [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient session header (lowercase)\n1091: - [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient execute command timeout handling\n1092: - [ ] CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient file operations\n1093: - [ ] AgentRuntimeClient session bootstrap\n1094: - [ ] AgentRuntimeClient invoke delegation\n1095: - [ ] AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient base URL and headers\n1096: - [ ] Exception hierarchy correct inheritance\n1097: - [ ] Package exports match __all__\n1098: - [ ] Utility functions work correctly\n1099: - [ ] Integration tests cover full lifecycle\n\n(End of file - total 1099 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec.md — AR-040 Python SDK/CLI Tests\n\n## AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI Tests\n\n**Module:** sdk-python/tests  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base specs:** python-sdk/design.md, python-sdk/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\