{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775901663622,"sessionID":"ses_2840505bcffecELQTfkh1K5DKB","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfce181001muftBSbSPBvI1N","messageID":"msg_d7bfcd177001nvKdZ7iM938Uy0","sessionID":"ses_2840505bcffecELQTfkh1K5DKB","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775901764743,"sessionID":"ses_2840505bcffecELQTfkh1K5DKB","part":{"id":"prt_d7bfe6be7001PjSSOVznZE874I","messageID":"msg_d7bfcd177001nvKdZ7iM938Uy0","sessionID":"ses_2840505bcffecELQTfkh1K5DKB","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7033d5eb483d45009cd4d10fede727e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: E2E Integration Tests for client-go\n\n**AR:** AR-041 — E2E 集成测试  \n**Module:** test/e2e  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Clientset Construction and Interface Compliance\n\n### Description\n\nClientset must be constructable from REST config and implement the Interface correctly.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Create Clientset from REST config\n- **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes REST config with cluster endpoint and credentials\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfig` is called with the config\n- **THEN** a non-nil `*Clientset` is returned with no error\n- **AND** the clientset implements the `Interface` interface\n- **AND** `RuntimeV1alpha1()` returns a valid `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n\n#### Scenario: Create Clientset with custom HTTP client\n- **GIVEN** a valid REST config and a custom `*http.Client` with custom timeouts\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfigAndClient` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `*Clientset` uses the provided HTTP client\n- **AND** all API calls use the custom client configuration\n\n#### Scenario: Clientset Discovery interface works\n- **GIVEN** a Clientset connected to a running Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** `Discovery()` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `DiscoveryInterface` can list API groups\n- **AND** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` is discoverable\n\n#### Scenario: Panics on invalid config with NewForConfigOrDie\n- **GIVEN** an invalid REST config (nil or missing required fields)\n- **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie` is called\n- **THEN** the function panics\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: AgentRuntime CRUD Operations\n\n### Description\n\nAgentRuntimeInterface must support full CRUD lifecycle against a live cluster.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Create an AgentRuntime resource\n- **GIVEN** a Clientset connected to a Kubernetes cluster with CRDs installed\n- **AND** a valid `AgentRuntime` spec in namespace `test-ns`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntime` has the correct name and namespace\n- **AND** the resource exists in the cluster with `kubectl get agentruntime`\n\n#### Scenario: Get an existing AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists in namespace `test-ns`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(ctx, \"test-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntime` has name `test-agent`\n- **AND** the spec matches the created resource\n\n#### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n- **GIVEN** three AgentRuntimes exist in namespace `test-ns`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntimeList` contains exactly 3 items\n- **AND** all items have namespace `test-ns`\n\n#### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes with label selector\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes exist with labels `app=test` and `app=prod`\n- **WHEN** `List` is called with `ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=test\"}`\n- **THEN** only AgentRuntimes with `app=test` label are returned\n\n#### Scenario: Update an AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists with `spec.replicas=1`\n- **WHEN** the spec is updated to `replicas=3` and `Update` is called\n- **THEN** the returned AgentRuntime has `spec.replicas=3`\n- **AND** the resource in cluster reflects the update\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateStatus subresource\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with empty status\n- **WHEN** `UpdateStatus` is called with status conditions set\n- **THEN** only the status subresource is updated\n- **AND** the spec remains unchanged\n\n#### Scenario: Delete an AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists\n- **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, \"test-agent\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the error is nil\n- **AND** subsequent `Get` returns a `NotFound` error\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteCollection with selector\n- **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntimes exist with label `cleanup=true`\n- **WHEN** `DeleteCollection` is called with matching label selector\n- **THEN** all matching resources are deleted\n- **AND** non-matching resources remain\n\n#### Scenario: Patch an AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `spec.replicas=1`\n- **WHEN** `Patch` is called with `MergePatchType` and JSON patch data `{\"spec\":{\"replicas\":5}}`\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime is updated with `spec.replicas=5`\n\n#### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime changes\n- **GIVEN** a Watch is started with `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n- **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created, updated, and deleted\n- **THEN** the watch channel receives `ADDED`, `MODIFIED`, and `DELETED` events respectively\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: CodeInterpreter CRUD Operations\n\n### Description\n\nCodeInterpreterInterface must support full CRUD lifecycle against a live cluster.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Create a CodeInterpreter resource\n- **GIVEN** a Clientset and valid `CodeInterpreter` spec\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreters(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter is created in the cluster\n\n#### Scenario: Full CRUD cycle for CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** a clean namespace\n- **WHEN** Create, Get, Update, UpdateStatus, List, and Delete operations are performed\n- **THEN** all operations complete successfully\n- **AND** the final state matches expectations\n\n#### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n- **GIVEN** a Watch is started for CodeInterpreters\n- **WHEN** multiple CodeInterpreters are created concurrently\n- **THEN** all `ADDED` events are received on the watch channel\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter List across namespaces\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters exist in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n- **WHEN** `List` is called in each namespace\n- **THEN** correct resources are returned per namespace\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: SharedInformerFactory Operations\n\n### Description\n\nSharedInformerFactory must correctly start, sync, and shutdown informers.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Start and Shutdown informer factory\n- **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with a Clientset\n- **WHEN** `Start(stopCh)` is called\n- **THEN** informers begin syncing\n- **AND** calling `Shutdown()` stops all informers gracefully\n\n#### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync reports sync status\n- **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n- **WHEN** `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` is called\n- **THEN** the returned map contains `true` for both types\n- **AND** all caches are synced with the cluster\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer and lister work together\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer started and synced\n- **AND** an AgentRuntime `test-ar` exists in `test-ns`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes().Lister().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(\"test-ar\")` is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime is returned from cache (no API call)\n- **AND** the object matches the cluster state\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer and lister work together\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer started and synced\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreters().Lister().List(labels.Everything())` is called\n- **THEN** all CodeInterpreters across namespaces are returned from cache\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace-scoped informer factory\n- **GIVEN** `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithNamespace(\"limited-ns\")`\n- **WHEN** informers are started\n- **THEN** only resources in `limited-ns` are cached\n- **AND** resources in other namespaces are not visible to the lister\n\n#### Scenario: Custom resync period\n- **GIVEN** a factory created with `defaultResync=30*time.Second`\n- **WHEN** informers run for longer than resync period\n- **THEN** full resync events are triggered periodically\n\n#### Scenario: ForResource returns correct informer\n- **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory\n- **WHEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"))` is called\n- **THEN** a GenericInformer for AgentRuntimes is returned\n- **AND** the informer is the same instance as from `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n\n#### Scenario: TweakListOptions filters list calls\n- **GIVEN** a factory with `WithTweakListOptions` that sets `LabelSelector`\n- **WHEN** the informer performs list operations\n- **THEN** only resources matching the selector are cached\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: Lister Operations\n\n### Description\n\nListers must provide efficient cached access to resources.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister lists across namespaces\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeLister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n- **THEN** all AgentRuntimes from both namespaces are returned\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister filters by namespace\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"ns-a\").List(labels.Everything())` is called\n- **THEN** only AgentRuntimes in `ns-a` are returned\n\n#### Scenario: Lister returns error for non-existent resource\n- **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `nonexistent` in namespace `test-ns`\n- **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(\"nonexistent\")` is called\n- **THEN** an error is returned (not nil)\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister mirrors AgentRuntimeLister behavior\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters in multiple namespaces\n- **WHEN** both `List` and `Get` operations are performed\n- **THEN** behavior matches AgentRuntimeLister patterns\n\n#### Scenario: Lister List with label selector\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes with various labels\n- **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector\n- **THEN** only matching resources are returned\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: Fake Clientset for Unit Testing\n\n### Description\n\nFake clientset must track objects and support testing patterns.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Fake clientset tracks objects\n- **GIVEN** `NewSimpleClientset()` creates an empty fake clientset\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimes are created via the fake client\n- **THEN** `List` returns all created objects\n- **AND** no actual API calls are made\n\n#### Scenario: Fake clientset returns injected errors\n- **GIVEN** a fake clientset with a reactor that returns errors\n- **WHEN** Create/Update/Delete operations are called\n- **THEN** the injected error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Fake clientset supports Watch\n- **GIVEN** a fake clientset with an AgentRuntime\n- **WHEN** `Watch` is called and the object is modified via the fake client\n- **THEN** watch events are generated and sent to the watcher\n\n#### Scenario: Fake clientset AddReactor captures actions\n- **GIVEN** a fake clientset with an AddReactor for \"create\"\n- **WHEN** Create is called\n- **THEN** the reactor captures the action\n- **AND** custom behavior can be implemented\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: Error Handling and Edge Cases\n\n### Description\n\nClient must handle Kubernetes API errors correctly.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Context cancellation aborts operations\n- **GIVEN** a context that is cancelled before API call completes\n- **WHEN** any CRUD operation is called with the cancelled context\n- **THEN** the operation returns a context cancellation error\n\n#### Scenario: NotFound error for missing resource\n- **GIVEN** no resource named `missing` exists\n- **WHEN** `Get(ctx, \"missing\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** a `*errors.StatusError` with status code 404 is returned\n\n#### Scenario: AlreadyExists error on duplicate create\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime `duplicate` already exists\n- **WHEN** `Create` is called with the same name\n- **THEN** an `AlreadyExists` error is returned\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid field errors are structured\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with an invalid spec field\n- **WHEN** `Create` is called\n- **THEN** the error can be cast to `*errors.StatusError`\n- **AND** `Status().Details.Causes` contains field-level error details\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout error on slow API\n- **GIVEN** a context with short deadline\n- **AND** API server is slow\n- **WHEN** operation is called\n- **THEN** timeout error is returned\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: Concurrent Operations\n\n### Description\n\nClient must handle concurrent operations safely.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent creates succeed with unique names\n- **GIVEN** a Clientset and 10 goroutines each creating an AgentRuntime\n- **AND** each goroutine uses a unique name\n- **WHEN** all goroutines complete\n- **THEN** all 10 AgentRuntimes exist in the cluster\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent reads from informer cache\n- **GIVEN** an informer with synced cache\n- **WHEN** 100 concurrent `Lister.Get` calls are made\n- **THEN** all calls complete without race conditions\n- **AND** data remains consistent\n\n#### Scenario: Watch handles high event throughput\n- **GIVEN** a Watch started on AgentRuntimes\n- **WHEN** 100 AgentRuntimes are created rapidly\n- **THEN** all 100 `ADDED` events are received\n- **AND** no events are dropped\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent updates with conflict resolution\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with multiple concurrent updates\n- **WHEN** some updates conflict due to resource version\n- **THEN** conflict errors are returned for stale updates\n- **AND** retry succeeds with fresh resource version\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: Resource Version and Optimistic Concurrency\n\n### Description\n\nClient must support Kubernetes optimistic concurrency control.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Update fails with stale resource version\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `resourceVersion=v1`\n- **AND** the resource was updated by another client (now `v2`)\n- **WHEN** an Update is attempted with `resourceVersion=v1`\n- **THEN** a conflict error is returned\n- **AND** the error status code is 409\n\n#### Scenario: Get with ResourceVersion returns consistent snapshot\n- **GIVEN** a valid `resourceVersion` from a previous list\n- **WHEN** `Get` is called with `metav1.GetOptions{ResourceVersion: rv}`\n- **THEN** the data is consistent with that resource version\n\n#### Scenario: List with ResourceVersion\n- **GIVEN** a resourceVersion from a previous list\n- **WHEN** `List` is called with that ResourceVersion\n- **THEN** response includes matching ResourceVersion\n- **AND** data is consistent with requested version\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: Integration with Kubernetes Ecosystem\n\n### Description\n\nclient-go must integrate with common Kubernetes patterns and tools.\n\n### Acceptance Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario: Works with controller-runtime\n- **GIVEN** a controller-runtime Manager\n- **WHEN** the client-go Clientset is used alongside controller-runtime\n- **THEN** both clients can operate on the same AgentRuntime resources\n- **AND** no conflicts occur\n\n#### Scenario: Informer integrates with workqueue\n- **GIVEN** an informer and a `workqueue.TypedRateLimitingInterface`\n- **WHEN** an Add/Update/Delete handler enqueues the key\n- **THEN** the workqueue processes keys in order with rate limiting\n\n#### Scenario: Metrics endpoint exposes informer stats\n- **GIVEN** a metrics registry and an informer factory\n- **WHEN** informer metrics are registered\n- **THEN** cache hits, misses, and sync duration are exposed as metrics\n\n#### Scenario: Leader election with informer factory\n- **GIVEN** a leader election lock\n- **WHEN** leader is elected\n- **THEN** informer factory starts\n- **AND** when leader lost, factory shuts down\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n|--------|-----------|------------|\n| REQ-001 | Clientset Construction | 4 |\n| REQ-002 | AgentRuntime CRUD | 10 |\n| REQ-003 | CodeInterpreter CRUD | 4 |\n| REQ-004 | SharedInformerFactory | 8 |\n| REQ-005 | Lister Operations | 5 |\n| REQ-006 | Fake Clientset | 4 |\n| REQ-007 | Error Handling | 5 |\n| REQ-008 | Concurrent Operations | 4 |\n| REQ-009 | Resource Version | 3 |\n| REQ-010 | Ecosystem Integration | 4 |\n\n**Total Scenarios:** 51\n\n---\n\n## Test Infrastructure\n\n### E2E Test Setup\n\n```go\n// test/e2e/e2e_test.go\npackage e2e\n\nimport (\n    \"testing\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    clientset \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n)\n\nfunc newTestClientset(t *testing.T) clientset.Interface {\n    loadingRules := clientcmd.NewDefaultClientConfigLoadingRules()\n    configOverrides := &clientcmd.ConfigOverrides{}\n    config, err := clientcmd.NewNonInteractiveDeferredLoadingClientConfig(\n        loadingRules, configOverrides).ClientConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"Failed to load kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n    }\n    cs, err := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        t.Fatalf(\"Failed to create clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n    return cs\n}\n\nfunc newTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n    }\n}\n\nfunc newTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n    return &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      name,\n            Namespace: namespace,\n        },\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Test Tags\n\n```go\n// +build e2e\n// Run: go test -tags=e2e ./test/e2e/...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client library |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | API machinery |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller patterns (optional) |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Clientset construction from REST config\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CRUD operations against live cluster\n- [ ] CodeInterpreter CRUD operations against live cluster\n- [ ] SharedInformerFactory Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync\n- [ ] Informer integration with Listers\n- [ ] Namespace-scoped informer filtering\n- [ ] Lister Get/List operations\n- [ ] Fake clientset object tracking\n- [ ] Error handling (NotFound, AlreadyExists, Conflict)\n- [ ] Context cancellation handling\n- [ ] Concurrent operations safety\n- [ ] Watch event reception\n- [ ] Resource version conflict detection\n- [ ] Integration with controller-runtime\n- [ ] Integration with workqueue patterns","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775901764594,"end":1775901764741}}}}
